problem: Simplify $$2\cos^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i).$$Note: The logarithms are with respect to base $e.$
model_solution:
Step 1: Since $\cos^2 x=1-\sin^2 x$, we can rewrite the expression as $2-2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)$.
We have $\cos^2$ of the imaginary logarithm of 2009, and the $\sin$ of the imaginary $\log$ of 4036081.
Since $\cos^2 x=1-\sin^2 x$, we can rewrite the expression as $2-2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$.
$=2-2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$.
Step 2: 
$=2-2\left(\cos^2(\log(2009)i)\right)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$
$=2-2\left(1-\sin^2(\log(2009)i)\right)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$
$=2-2+2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$
$=2+2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$
$=2+2\sin^2(\log(2009)i)+i\sin(\log(4036081)i)$
$=2+2\sin^2\left(\log(2009)i\right)+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
$=2+2\sin\left(\log(2009)i\right)^2+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
$=2+2(-\cos\left(\log(2009)i\right))^2+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
$=2+2\cos^2\left(\log(2009)i\right)+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
$=2+2\cos^2\left(\log(2009)i\right)+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
$=2+2\cos^2\left(\log(2009)i\right)+i\sin\left(\log(4036081)i\right)$
